Batelco, Omantel, Qtel, Shuaa: Persian Gulf Equity Preview

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-09-15T05:06:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/batelco-omantel-and-qtel-persian-gulf-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Persian Gulf markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and prices are from the last close.  Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  advanced 0.4 percent, the most in
more than a week, while  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  slipped
0.2 percent.  Saudi Arabia ’s market is closed for the weekend.  Oman Telecommunications Co. (OTEL)  SAOG: The country’s
biggest telephone company obtained approval for a merger with
Oman Mobile. The shares declined 0.3 percent to 1.142 rials.  Qatar Telecom QSC (QTEL QD): The country’s biggest company
by revenue started an interconnection partnership with Bahrain
Telecommunications Co. (BATELCO BI), the state-controlled
company. Qatar Telecom shares rose 0.5 percent to 147.8 riyals
and Batelco shares were unchanged at 0.394 dinar.  Shuaa Capital PSC (SHUAA)  : The investment bank
controlled by Dubai’s ruler said it appointed advisers to
conduct due diligence on potential acquisitions. Shuaa has
narrowed down its targets to “a few” companies and plans to
close one or more deals before the end of the year. The shares
dropped 1.9 percent to 82.6 fils.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
